That is a somewhat different story. 

Blas is indeed an external interface, and just how you can make your R
processing faster by installing an optimised Blas library like Goto, Atlas,
Intel MKL, ... you can conceivably also gain by letting the GPU handle Blas.
But as the answer stated, that still involves going 'inside' and replacing
dgemm class (to Blas) with cublasDgemm (to GPU).

Moreover, trouble is that back in real-life, we are rarely seeing our _total
processing_ constrained by the Blas / linear algebra portion.  Plus, some
Blas are already using multiple cores so the net gain is small.

